## Review Checklist

### Correctness
- [ ] Logic is sound and handles edge cases
- [ ] Error handling is appropriate
- [ ] No obvious bugs or issues

### Code Quality
- [ ] Follows project coding conventions
- [ ] Uses existing patterns and abstractions
- [ ] No code duplication
- [ ] Appropriate naming and documentation

### Performance
- [ ] No obvious performance issues
- [ ] Efficient algorithms and data structures
- [ ] No unnecessary allocations or operations

### Security
- [ ] No security vulnerabilities
- [ ] Proper input validation
- [ ] Sensitive data handled appropriately

## Output Format

Provide a structured review with:

1. **Summary**: Overall assessment (Approve / Request Changes)
2. **Issues Found**: List any problems with severity (Critical / Major / Minor / Nitpick)
3. **Suggestions**: Improvements that could be made
4. **Positive Notes**: What was done well

## Review Approach

- Be constructive, not critical
- Explain the "why" behind suggestions
- Prioritize issues by impact
- Acknowledge good work
